-- Abbott Vows Not to Undo Labor's Industrial Relations Laws, Australian Says
-- Jacob Greber
-- 2010-07-16T22:02:27Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-16/abbott-vows-not-to-undo-labor-s-industrial-relations-laws-australian-says.html

          
          
             Australian opposition leader  Tony Abbott  will today pledge to retain the Labor government’s
industrial relations laws if he wins office in an election
likely to be called today, the  Australian  newspaper says.  
 Abbott will today tell a gathering of coalition supporters
in Brisbane that he won’t resurrect the former Liberal-National
government’s industrial relations policy, known as work choices,
the newspaper reported.  
